# identity

The seed protocol — how Constellary hands off session discoveries to the Theurgist
so that personal space and framework record both stay current. Solves the distillation
collapse discovered in the integration session (2026-03-09).

# what_it_does

Defines the structured handoff unit (the seed) that travels from Constellary to Theurgist
mid-session and at close. The seed carries routing information (personal / framework / both)
so the Theurgist knows exactly what to produce and where to put it.

Without this: rich sessions produce framework artifacts but personal space stays thin.
With this: every session-worthy moment has a clear path to the right artifact.

# the_seed_format

```
THEURGIST SEED
─────────────────────────────────────────
for:        personal | framework | both
what_moved: one sentence
why:        why this matters next session
orbits:     [circling questions]
action:     new-drop | update-drop | fold-only | both
─────────────────────────────────────────
```

# trigger_conditions

Fire a seed when:
- A decision is made that changes the space
- A realization lands the traveler will want to return to
- A project or intention arrives
- An orbit resolves or a new one opens
- A discovery surfaces through use (not hypothetical — lived)
- Session close — sweep for anything not yet captured

# routing_rules

```
personal realization    → firmament/space/drops/ + theurgist.fold
framework decision      → framework folds + framework/codex
meta-conversation       → framework/codex only (unless it moved the traveler)
both                    → split explicitly, never collapse
```

# what_it_produces

Every seed → exactly two outputs or none (two_output_discipline):
1. fold update — AI truth, dense, carried forward
2. compiled drop — user anchor, traveler's register, Pixelverse reads this

# state

designed: yes — protocol is defined in constellary.fold + theurgist.fold (v0.2)
implemented: partially — the entities know the protocol, but it runs on AI judgment
             not on a formal trigger. Next step: consistent use in sessions.
needs_build: no mechanical build required. behavioral protocol.
             Future: session close sweep could become a slash command or MCP trigger.

# orbits

- slash-command-for-session-close — `/sweep` or `/close` that triggers Constellary to
  run the sweep and fire seeds. Removes the reliance on remembering. (state: open)
- mcp-trigger — could the session close sweep be automated via a hook? (state: open)

